Table.SCRIPT: The English Channel is a sea in [{Europe}]. It is between southern England and [{northern}] France. The [{Strait}] of Dover is the shortest [{distance}] in the English Channel. In 1994, a train that travels in a [{tunnel}] opened. This tunnel [{allows}] people to go under the Strait of Dover. After the “Chunnel” opened, it was [{possible}] to cross the English Channel in thirty-five minutes. The name comes from putting “channel” and “tunnel” together. The Chunnel allows people to travel between England and France quickly and easily.
Table.TITLE: The Chunnel
